	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Guide: Marloss Berry</h1>
	
	<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
		<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From The Cataclysm: Dark Days Ahead Wiki</div>
		<div id="contentSub"></div>
		
		
		
		<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
		<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</a>
		<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><pre><b>For information about a more recent version like <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/0.C_(Cooper)" title="0.C (Cooper)">0.C (Cooper)</a> this <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://discourse.cataclysmdda.org/t/how-do-i-mycus-spoilers/7534">forum topic</a> might help.</b><br />
Or read this <b><a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Guide:_Mycus" title="Guide: Mycus">In-character Mycus guide</a>. Warning spoilers!</b>
</pre>
<pre><b>Guide based on the 02Feb Bugfix version of Cataclysm DDA, with minor updates from <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/0.5" title="0.5">0.5</a>.</b>
Some of the information present here might not apply to future versions.
</pre>
<table style="text-align: left; margin: 1em 0; border: 1px solid purple; border-left:4px solid; padding: .2em 1em .2em 0.6em; border-radius: 0 .7em .7em 0; -moz-border-radius: 0 .7em .7em 0; -webkit-border-radius: 0 .7em .7em 0; background: #FFF0FF; font: 1.1em Consolas, monospace; color: purple;">
<tbody><tr>
<td><b>WARNING: This page may contain spoilers and ruin the joy of adventure.</b><br />Remember, it is not 'dying' it is 'learning how to do better next time'!
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>Can be found randomly on NPC's, or in the world map. One berry spawns per Marloss bush; bushes can occur near netherworld portals (not the ones that have rubble) and Fungal Blooms.  There will generally be 0-2 bushes per bloom; each of the roughly 400 tiles has a 1/300 chance of being a Marloss bush. Portals will be guarded by some wandering nether monsters.
</p>
