<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Mechanics">Mechanics</span></h2>
<p>NOTE: The Mechanics have been changed at some point and the below is not up to date
</p><p>It has no effect when eaten by NPC's.
</p><p>First, the code checks whether the player also has the "Marloss Carrier" mutation. When not carrying the mutation, It has one of the following effects:
</p>
<ul><li>33% chance. Gives one <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Mutation" title="Mutation">Mutation</a>. Gives the "This berry tastes extremely strange!" text</li>
<li>22% chance. <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Mutation" title="Mutation">Purifies</a> the consumer as if the consumer consumed a purifier, removes 30 pain. Gives the "This berry makes you feel better all over." text</li>
<li>11% chance. <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Mutation" title="Mutation">Purifies</a> the consumer as if the consumer consumed a purifier, removes 30 pain, and removes radiation. Gives the "This berry makes you feel better all over." text</li>
<li>11% chance. Fully satiates the consumer. Gives the "This berry is delicious, and very filling!" text</li>
<li>11% chance. Makes the consumer vomit. Gives the "You take one bite, and immediately vomit!" text</li>
<li>11% chance. Success! The consumer is now a Marloss Carrier. Gives the "You feel a strange warmth spreading throughout your body..." text</li></ul>
<p>Non-carriers, no matter the result--even if you immediately vomit--enjoy the berry, for roughly +59 Morale per berry.
</p><p>If the player is a Marloss Carrier, eating another berry does quite a bit:
</p>
<ul><li>gives the typical Morale bonus</li>
<li>inspires Marloss Bliss (+100 Morale)</li>
<li>fully Sates the Carrier</li>
<li>spawns netherworld Marloss plants (which will not include berries), fungus, and slime patches around the consumer.  A few friendly Blobs may show up as well.</li></ul>
<p>This last "marlossify" process can even break through walls.  Fortunately, the effect does not harm any items that may be present.  Marloss Carriers are advised to consume berries away from their base and to space them out, so as not to trap themselves in large fungal growths.
</p><p>"As you eat the berry, you have a near-religious experience, feeling at one with your surroundings..."
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Marloss_Carrier">Marloss Carrier</span></h2>
<div id="Marloss_Carrier" style="display:table; margin: 1.2em 0 0.6em 0; font-family: consolas"><span style="font-size: 1.3em;"><b><a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Marloss_Carrier" title="Marloss Carrier">Marloss Carrier</a></b></span> <span style="font-size: 0.7em;">MARLOSS</span>&#160;<a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Mutation#Sources_of_mutation" title="Mutation"><b style="border:1px solid darkblue; color:blue; padding: 0 0.6em">Targeted Mutation Only</b></a>&#160;<a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Purifier" title="Purifier"><b style="border:1px solid darkblue; background-color:lightblue; color:darkblue; padding: 0 0.6em">Not purifiable</b></a>&#160;<a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Marloss" title="Marloss"><b style="border:1px solid black; background-color:purple; color:white; padding: 0 0.6em">MARLOSS</b></a>
<table border="0" class="va-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border: 0px none; margin: 0 auto 0 1.5em; text-align:left;">

<tbody><tr>
<td style="border-left: 3px solid darkgreen; border-top: 1px solid darkgreen; padding: 0.1em 0.5em">Point cost: <span style="color:green"><b>4</b></span>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td style="max-width:64em; border-left: 1px solid darkgreen; padding: 0.1em 0.5em 0">"Ever since you ate that Marloss berry, you can't get its scent out of your nose, and you have a strong desire to try some seeds and… sap?"
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td style="max-width:64em; border-left: 1px solid darkgreen; padding: 0.1em 0.5em 0">
</td></tr></tbody></table>
</div>
<p>Now you are something less, or more, than human. Eating Marloss berries will result in the effect described above.
</p><p>Marloss Carrier is as vulnerable to <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Purifier" title="Purifier">Purifier</a> as any other <a href="/cdda_wiki/index.php/Mutation" title="Mutation">Mutation</a>.
</p>
